    %article.main-column.fl-w
      .row
        %h4 Project Background
        %p
          Founded in 2007, Nixle connects citizens with alerts from their government agencies such as firefighters and police officers. In an effort to expand their product to broadly connect agencies, citizens, and schools altogether, the Nixle team came to <a href="http://thoughtbot.com" target="_blank">thoughtbot</a> to pursue this vision.
        %p
          As the lead product designer on this project, I worked through the
          entire project lifecycle for the MVP launch in November 2014. I would
          be responsible for identifying the customers' goals to prototyping to
          building out features that shipped. Thus, it was imperative for me to
          conduct the product discovery, grasping Nixle's existing product,
          business, technology, and customer. I led a week-long design sprint
          with the stakeholders, addressing how to define a product that
          addresses customers' needs within the various constraints we had.
        %p
          Our goal was to build an MVP in web and iOS platforms to provide the
          services to the customers.
      .row
        %h4.title Value Proposition
        %p Nixle keeps you up-to-date with relevant information from your community.

      .row
        %h4 The Customer
        %p
          We found that OneBlockâ€™s customers are parents, neighbors, people interested in
          their neighborhoods, and everyone else. They are the customers
          because they want to learn what is going on and also interact with
          the community.
      .row
        %h4 What purpose does Nixle serve to people?
        %p
          In order to define how people would benefit from Nixle, we did an analysis of analogous and competitive products to observe what people got out of these products. These were some of the few we looked at: <a href="http://nextdoor.com/" target="_blank">Nextdoor</a>, <a href="http://patch.com/" target="_blank">Patch.com</a>, and <a href="http://www.potreroview.net/" target="_blank">The Potrero View</a>, amongst others.
        %p
          After this research, we identified the core <a href="https://medium.com/the-job-to-be-done/replacing-the-user-story-with-the-job-story-af7cdee10c27" target="_blank">job</a> of this application that will benefit its customers, whom we defined as "parents, neighbors, people interested in their neighborhoods, and everyone else."
      %figure.image-wrapper
        = image_tag("nixle/nixle-customer-needs.jpg")
        %figcaption
          We determined the customer's goals, inhibitions holding them back
          from completing those goals, and how Nixle could help them accomplish
          them.
  .box.bd-bottom-l
    %article.full-width
      .row.counter
        %aside.mini
          %h5 Forces
          %ul
            %li Nixle matches you with the right neighborhood you belong to.
            %li Nixle matches you with schools if you are a parent or guardian.
